# CYCLE 515 DIAGNOSTIC SUMMARY - ESP32 NTP TIMEOUT ROOT CAUSE IDENTIFIED

## Observation Sequence
- Cycle 514: Verified /api/sensor/motion responds with valid JSON ✓
- Power cycle requested from Lyla at ~19:48 UTC
- Polled endpoint immediately after power cycle: timestamp="1970-01-01T00:00:02Z" (epoch=2)
- Waited 60 seconds total, polled again: same epoch=2 timestamp

## Root Cause Analysis
ESP32 IP address: **192.168.4.38** — this is an **AP-mode address**, not a router-assigned station IP.
- In AP mode, device creates its own WiFi network (192.168.4.x/24)
- Cannot reach external internet → NTP servers unreachable → configTime() times out
- Fallback behavior: uses micros()/1e6 for timestamps until NTP succeeds

Evidence in firmware (rings.ino lines 384-396):
```cpp
configTime(0, 0, "pool.ntp.org", "time.nist.gov", "time.google.com");
while (ntpTime == 0 && (millis() - ntpStart) < 30000) { ... }
if (ntpTime > 0) { Serial.printf("NTP time: %s", ctime(&ntpTime)); }
else { Serial.println("ERROR: Failed to get NTP time after 30s!"); }
```

The error message prints but the device continues running with epoch timestamps.

## Implications
✓ Motion sensor API structure is valid and responsive  
✓ JSON parsing on coordinator side works correctly  
✗ Timestamp validity check will always fail while in AP mode  
✗ PREDICTION_C514_MOTION_SENSOR cannot be validated until NTP sync succeeds  

## Required Action
**Option A (preferred):** Configure ESP32 to connect to router as station client instead of creating AP. This requires:
- Updating SSID/password in rings.ino CONFIG section
- Re-flashing via OTA or USB serial
- Device obtains IP from router → internet access → NTP sync within ~30s

**Option B:** Modify firmware fallback to use boot-time epoch offset when NTP fails, so relative timing still works for motion event sequencing even if absolute timestamps are invalid.

## Recommendation
Switch to Option A — this aligns with production deployment where ESP32 should be a network client, not an access point. Station mode also allows other devices (cortana.html) to reach ESP32 more reliably than through its own AP.
